To me, the principle of accumulation is

01:05:02.890 --> 01:05:06.680
one of the fundamental principles I bring
to understanding what's happening

01:05:06.710 --> 01:05:10.760
in creation,
that the universe is accumulating.

01:05:10.790 --> 01:05:12.600
It's learning.

01:05:12.630 --> 01:05:14.240
It's a self-learning system.

01:05:14.270 --> 01:05:16.520
And so we are constantly learning.

01:05:16.550 --> 01:05:17.860
We can't help but learn.

01:05:17.890 --> 01:05:19.800
Even if we do a mediocre job in our

01:05:19.800 --> 01:05:22.040
lifetime, we're still
learning in that lifetime.

01:05:22.040 --> 01:05:24.040
And if we do a better job, we're learning.

01:05:24.070 --> 01:05:26.460
And as we learn, we activate.

01:05:26.490 --> 01:05:32.400
In one sense, I think we are learning
to be geniuses in every area of life.

01:05:32.430 --> 01:05:34.880
A genius at chess,

01:05:34.910 --> 01:05:40.040
a genius at relationships, a genius
in all the different areas of life.

01:05:40.070 --> 01:05:46.980
And it's as if each lifetime is a petal
in a flower, the soul is the flower.

01:05:47.010 --> 01:05:48.482
And their-- if you just--

01:05:48.682 --> 01:05:52.840
I meditate sometimes on a flower
and imagine each hundred-year-lifetime is

01:05:52.870 --> 01:05:58.940
a pistil, and a stamen,
and a petal in this magnificent flower.

01:05:58.970 --> 01:06:02.400
And that's, you know-- to
be a genius at life,

01:06:02.430 --> 01:06:07.620
to really to be completely unfolded, and
taking advantage of the opportunity

01:06:07.650 --> 01:06:11.210
that we've been given to grow
and become more than we've been.

01:06:11.240 --> 01:06:15.920
And, again,
so many-- even though many cultures have

01:06:15.950 --> 01:06:20.100
understood reincarnation, I
don't think they've grasped it fully.

01:06:20.130 --> 01:06:25.240
They haven't really seen the
full potential of the concept.

01:06:25.270 --> 01:06:29.440
They've really seen it within an early
limitation of it.

